title: Patcher Issue (Tried Common Solutions)
body:
Hi,

I double click to launch League (Currently running as administrator). The LoL icon with a gray bar appears, then it disappears and nothing happens. I have tried deleting certain files from the folders and re-installing, but nothings been working so far.

I'm not sure what I should attach so I'll put (1) rads_user_kernal file and (2) the latest file from Patcher Logs 

Many many thanks for your help!
-Vertibrae

replies.body: Unfortunately, these logs don't tell me a whole lot other than make a huge wall. At what percent in the patcher are you specifically getting an error?  Also, is this on the legacy or updated client?  Let me know!

IMG: http://apollo-eu-uploads.s3.amazonaws.com/1429364020691/Untitled.png

That flashes briefly and then it closes. Nothing happens after that.

Thanks for your follow-up!  It seems like the patcher isn't coming up at all then, in which case a security setting or program might be blocking the patch from launching.  Go over each step of the [permissions](https://support.riotgames.com/hc/en-us/articles/204134104-Setting-up-your-Permissions) guide to make sure the patcher has access to load to fix it up.  I hope that helps!
